    "CLEFIA was implemented over FPGAs for innovation given their favourable circumstances regarding computation adaptability, time to showcase, advancement expenses, and organization time for committed solutions [27,53].FeW: FeW is an innovative, lightweight block cipher designed for software-based systems.",
    "It operates on 64-bit plaintext and generates 64-bit ciphertext over 32 rounds.",
    "FEW incorporates a combination of Feistel and generalized Feistel structures to enhance security against simple cryptographic attacks.",
    "Moreover, FEW demonstrates resistance to linear and zero correlation attacks, ensuring robust protection for the design [54].",
    "HIGHT:The HIGHT algorithm is suitable for low-resource devices."
